Interface JasmParserListener

public interface JasmParserListener
A listener to be notified of events while parsing jasm code. An instance of this interface must be supplied when constructing a JasmParser. These callback methods take StringView objects rather than bare Strings to help in creating helpful diagnostic messages. All the methods have default implementations that do nothing.

  • Method Details

    • exceptionOccurred

      default void exceptionOccurred(JasmParser parser, JasmSyntaxException ex)
      Notifies the listener that an exception has occurred while parsing due to some sort of error in the code. This method may be called with the parser in any state.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser that encountered an error
      ex - the error that occurred

    • sourceDirective

      default void sourceDirective(JasmParser parser, StringView source)
      Notifies the listener that a .source directive has been encountered. This method will only be called when the parser is in its initial global state.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser
      source - the source filename from the directive

    • classDirective

      default void classDirective(JasmParser parser, StringView classId, List<StringView> flags, StringView className)
      Notifies the listener that a .class/.interface/.enum directive has been encountered. This method will only be called when the parser is in its initial global state.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser
      classId - the type of class from the directive (either ".class", ".interface", or ".enum"
      flags - the flags that were included in the directive such as "public" and "static".
      className - the class name specified in the directive

    • superDirective

      default void superDirective(JasmParser parser, StringView superName)
      Notifies the listener that a .super directive has been encountered. This method will only be called when the parser is in its initial global state.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser
      superName - the name of the superclass from the directive

    • implementsDirective

      default void implementsDirective(JasmParser parser, StringView interfaceName)
      Notifies the listener that an .implements directive has been encountered. This method will only be called when the parser is in its initial global state.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser
      interfaceName - the name of the superinterface from the directive

    • fieldDirective

      default void fieldDirective(JasmParser parser, List<StringView> flags, StringView name, StringView descriptor)
      Notifies the listener that a .field directive has been encountered. This method will only be called when the parser is in its initial global state.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser
      flags - any flags from the directive (such as "public" or "static")
      name - the field name from the directive
      descriptor - the type descriptor from the directive

    • methodDirective

      default void methodDirective(JasmParser parser, List<StringView> flags, StringView name, StringView descriptor)
      Notifies the listener that a .method directive has been encountered. This method will only be called when the parser is in its initial global state.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser
      flags - any flags from the directive (such as "public" or "static")
      name - the method name from the directive
      descriptor - the method type descriptor from the directive

    • codeDirective

      default void codeDirective(JasmParser parser)
      Notifies the listener that a .code directive has been encountered. Once this method has been called, the parser is in its code state, so only callbacks relevant to the code state will be called.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser

    • codeLabel

      default void codeLabel(JasmParser parser, StringView labelName)
      Notifies the listener that the parser has encountered a label. This method will only be called when the parser is in its code state.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser
      labelName - the name of the label

    • codeInstruction

      default void codeInstruction(JasmParser parser, StringView opcode, List<StringView> operands)
      Notifies the listener that the parser has encountered an instruction. This method will only be called when the parser is in its code state.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser
      opcode - the opcode (such as "istore_3" or "invokevirtual")
      operands - a list of any operands provided (may be empty)

    • endCodeDirective

      default void endCodeDirective(JasmParser parser)
      Notifies the listener that the parser has encountered an .end code directive. After this call the parser leaves its code state and reenters the initial global state.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser

    • tableDirective

      default void tableDirective(JasmParser parser)
      Notifies the listener that the parser has encountered a .table directive. After this call the parser enters its table state and only callbacks relevant to this state will be called.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser

    • tableLine

      default void tableLine(JasmParser parser, StringView label, StringView target)
      Notifies the listener that the parser has encountered one line of a table. This method will only be called when the parser is in its table state.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser
      label - the label of the table line
      target - the target of the table line

    • endTableDirective

      default void endTableDirective(JasmParser parser)
      Notifies the listener that the parser has encountered an .end table directive. After this call the parser leaves its table state and reenters the code state.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser

    • endOfInput

      default void endOfInput(JasmParser parser)
      Notifies the listener that the parser has exhausted the input. The parser will call no more methods of this listener.
      Parameters:
      parser - the parser
